properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 8 at 2:55PM CST until January 9 at 6:00PM CST by NWS La Crosse WI
properties.description:
...Slippery Travel Expected in Taylor County on Thursday...

.A light wintry mix of snow and freezing drizzle is expected to
fall across Taylor County in north central Wisconsin on Thursday.
Total ice accumulation up to a tenth of an inch is expected with
little to no snow accumulation.

Plan on slippery road conditions on Thursday which could impact
the morning and evening commutes. Slow down and use caution while
traveling.

* WHAT...A light wintry mix is expected. Total ice accumulation up
to a tenth of an inch and little to no snow accumulation.

* WHERE...Taylor County.

* WHEN...From 8 AM to 6 PM CST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning and evening commutes.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions can be obtained from Wisconsin 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 8 AM TO 6 PM CST THURSDAY
